<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   Armed Forces Deactivate Bombs in Quiche </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1502045594 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 2152 GMT 14 Feb 
93 </F>

<F P=103> PA1502045594 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Guatemala City, 14 Feb (NOTIMEX) -- The National 
Police have disclosed at least three explosive devices were 
deactivated today by members of the Guatemalan Armed Forces in 
the northwestern Department (province) of Quiche. 
  Three bombs were placed along public light posts in the 
Chichicastenango Municipality, 200 km northeast of Guatemala 
City, and deactivated by Army specialists. The police report 
adds Army troops are searching the area, attempting to locate 
the terrorists. 
  According to police, a knapsack with explosive devices and 
documents linking guerrillas to the attempts were found in the 
area where the explosives were discovered. 
  The deactivation took place after three electricity high 
tension wire pylons were sabotaged less than 48 hours in the 
same area of Quiche. 
  Nine electricity high tension pylons have been destroyed 
with 
dynamite charges in the western Department of Quetzaltenango, 
Solola, and Quiche. 
  The Government Ministry and Army are trying to locate those 
responsible for these incidents. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

