<H3> <TI>   Defense Secretariat Denies Involvement in Slayings </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1402175794 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1402175794 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Good Morning From Mexico" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The National Defense Secretariat has issued a 
bulletin denying the Mexican Army's alleged participation in the 
murder of three people in the area of Morelia, Altamirano, 
Chiapas State. 
  In reply to a request made by various political and human 
rights organizations that requested clarification of the 
incident, the National Defense Secretariat said the Mexican Army 
never carried out any action to arrest, much less to murder 
these individuals, given that on 7 January there was no military 
presence in the area. 
  The Defense Secretariat added that at the request of the 
people, the Army arrested 32 individuals who had broken the law, 
clarifying that this occurred five days after the armed 
confrontation began. The Army turned over the 32 arrested 
individuals to local authorities after a public medical 
examination was made to determine their physical condition, the 
bulletin concluded. 

</TEXT>

