<F P=100> Colombia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Visiting Peruvian President Denies Negotiations With Shining 
Path </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1502025094 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 2054 GMT 14 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1502025094 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Santa Fe de Bogota, 14 Feb (NOTIMEX) -- Peruvian 
President Alberto Fujimori, who arrived in Colombia today, 
denied having conducted any negotiations whatsoever with the 
Shining Path, and he reiterated he will continue to implement 
harsh measures against that organization. 
  "We have made no contact with the terrorist leaders who are 
free," Fujimori said, denying Lima newspaper reports stating the 
government and Shining Path are holding meetings aimed at 
initiating a dialogue. 
  During a news conference, the Peruvian president added: "We 
have established contact via our intelligence services to 
capture their leaders but not to establish communication, let 
alone establish talks." 
  "The policy of my government is to capture the terrorists or 
confront and annihilate them," said the Peruvian head of state. 
  Fujimori warned: "I will not allow terrorists to continue 
perpetrating so many murders, and that is why we have adopted 
adequate measures, some of them harsh but effective." 
  According to official figures, the Maoist organization has 
caused the death of 25,000 Peruvians. [passage omitted] 
  President Fujimori reiterated his support for the candidacy 
of his host to the post of OAS secretary general. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

