<H3> <TI>   Fidel Extends Hospitality to Collor </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0502162794 Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL in Portuguese 4 
Feb 94 p 6--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PY0502162794 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "JB Report" by Teodomiro Braga] </F>
  [Text] The Cuban Government has lied: former Brazilian 
President Fernando Collor, wife Rosane and their friends Luis 
Carlos Chaves and Eunicia Guimaraes stayed at Fidel Castro's 
guest house in Varadero, a sea resort. 
  For three days Cuban officials extended VIP treatment to 
Collor and his entourage despite the vehement denials of the 
Cuban Government. 
  Collor tried to see Fidel Castro but failed. The Cuban 
president chose to avoid him after receiving a number of 
telegrams of protest from the Workers Party and other Brazilian 
leftwing parties. 
  The former president stayed at a modest guest house located 
a 
few meters from the posh mansion which Al Capone, the gangster, 
used in the thirties. 
  Francisco Marchante, a bodyguard whom the Cuban Government 
had reportedly assigned to the former Brazilian president, 
accompanied Collor wherever he went in Cuba. 
  This episode undermined Fidel's credibility; the nickname 
Red 
Pinocchio suits him just fine. 

</TEXT>

