<H3> <TI>   Portugal Ratifies Extradition, Mutual Aid Treaties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0802173594 Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL in Portuguese 7 
Feb 94 p 7--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PY0802173594 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Diplomatic Report" column by Luiz Orlando </F>
Carneiro] 
  [Text] On 3 February, Portuguese President Mario Soares and 
the Portuguese Assembly of the Republic ratified the Extradition 
and Mutual Aid in Penal Matters treaties that were signed by the 
two countries. 
  The Extradition Treaty simplifies the formalities for the 
extradition of persons who have been sentenced to prison terms 
of more than one year in either country. 
  The Mutual Aid Treaty establishes cooperation rules between 
the two countries' judicial authorities. 

</TEXT>

