  [Text] No less than 16 Russian bankers have arrived in the 
country. Their main objective is to obtain detailed knowledge 
of our banking system's advanced computer network. 
  Through 10 February, the Russian bankers will be visiting 
Sao 
Paulo. They are going to visit Febraban [Brazilian Federation 
of Banks], Bradesco [Brazilian Discount Bank] installations, the 
Sao Paulo State Federation (Fiesp), the informatics department 
of Itau Bank, and the Sao Paulo Commercial Association. 
  The Russian bankers and executives represent the following 
financial organizations: Incombank, Promsstroibank, Roskombank, 
Unicombank, Chasprombank, Evrobank, Kuzbasprombank, Tarhany, 
Volgoprombank [all names as published], and the Mortgage 
Joint-Stock Bank [title in English]. 

