<H3> <TI>   Lage Arrives in Caracas; Leaves for Colombia 9 Feb </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0802204294 Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish 0035 GMT 8 Feb 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PA0802204294 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana PRENSA LATINA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Caracas, 7 Feb (PL) -- Today, Cuban Vice President 
Carlos Lage arrived in Caracas for a short visit in which he 
will meet with Rafael Caldera, the new Venezuelan head of state. 
  Tomorrow, Lage will also meet with Foreign Minister Miguel 
Angel Burelli Rivas, Venezuelan Investment Fund President Abdon 
Vivas Teran, representatives of the Venezuelan Petroleum 
Corporation, and local businessmen among others. 
  Lage just concluded a visit to Brazil. Upon his arrival in 
Caracas, Lage described his visit to Brazil as very 
satisfactory. PRENSA LATINA confirmed that Lage will travel to 
Colombia at the invitation of the Colombian Government in the 
early hours of 9 February. 

</TEXT>

