<H3> <TI>   French Businessmen, Executives To Study Business Prospects </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0602034294 Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish 1824 GMT 4 Feb 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PA0602034294 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana PRENSA LATINA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 4 Feb (PL) -- A group of French private 
businessmen and Cuban business executives will start meeting in 
Havana on 7 February to study business prospects for both 
countries in different sectors of the Cuban economy. 
  The visitors will be headed by Jean Pierre Desgeorges, vice 
president of the French National Sponsorship Council [Consejo 
Nacional de Patronato Frances] (CNPF), which is a collective 
that includes 225 organizations in the industrial, financial, 
and services sectors. 
  Cuban business sources consider this first CNPF visit as 
very 
important, because the collective represents approximately 1 
million French businessmen, including chiefs of state, 
ministers, and private and public leaders, and has 43 committees 
in several countries that operate under the management of 
important world business personalities. 
  At the meeting, which will continue until 10 February, the 
32 
members of the visiting delegation will hold talks and meet with 
Cuban executives who work in various economic sectors, such as 
construction material, tourism, transportation, electricity, and 
banks, among others. 
  Likewise, it is expected the French delegation will meet 
with 
top Cuban officials, including Carlos Lage, vice president of 
the Council of State; Osmany Cienfuegos, vice president of the 
Council of Ministers; and Roberto Robaina, the Cuban foreign 
minister. 

</TEXT>

