<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Honors Award-Winning Artists, Intellectuals </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0902204494 Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish 2245 GMT 7 Feb 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PA0902204494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana PRENSA LATINA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 7 Feb (PL) -- Culture Ministry sources 
announced today that 355 Cuban artists and intellectuals, both 
in and out of the country, received awards for professional 
excellence in 1993. 
  According to Lecsy Tejeda, president of the National Stage 
Arts Council, a long and varied list of creators, including 
poets Dulce Maria Loynaz (winner of the Cervantes literature 
prize) and Eliseo Diego and the musicians Leo Brouwer and 
Gonzalo Rubalcaba received international awards last year. 
  Prima ballerina Alicia Alonso, theater playwright Abelardo 
Estorino, film directors Alfredo Guevara and Tomas Gutierrez 
Alea, and cartoonist Roberto Fabelo also received important 
distinctions. 
  Other artists in less mentioned fields such as applied arts 
and the circus also received awards. 
  Despite the difficult economic situation in the country, 
which has compelled the government to eliminate or drastically 
reduce budgets, Cuban culture has been particularly productive 
during the past 12 months. 
  If the international awards are categorized by field, Tejada 
said, the plastic arts are at the head (42), followed by film 
making (33), theater arts (19), music (12), and literature (10). 
  In Tejada's opinion, the National Art Education System 
deserves a special mention because 23 of the people awarded are 
still students at its specialized centers yet they stood out for 
their talent and solid education. 
  To honor all those personalities -- both those who are 
established professionals as well as the newcomers -- there will 
be an art gala at the National Theater in Havana on 11 February. 
A complete rundown of the 1993 awards will be presented at that 
event. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

