<H3> <TI>   Raul Castro Attends Opening of Western Army Training </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1502202694 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1800 
GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1502202694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Relay from San Antonio de Los Banos Airbase by Reporter </F>
Jose Luis Martinez Zamora] 
  [Text] The new year of training for the Western Army began 
here in the presence of Army General Raul Castro, Minister of 
the FAR [Revolutionary Armed Forces]. The ceremony took place at 
the Playa Giron Air Brigade located in San Antonio de los Banos. 
  The Western Army's main objectives during the current 
training period will be: maintaining a high level of training 
and readiness; increasing the troops' self-sufficiency, 
supported by an intensive nutrition program; continuing the 
weapons and techniques preparedness program; and continuing to 
refurbish the theater of military operations. 
  During the ceremony, the defenders of the western territory 
ratified their decision to fight resolutely to achieve the title 
of best FAR command in 1995. 

</TEXT>

