<H3> <TI>   Cordoba Governor Wants To Run in 1995 Presidential Race </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1502133994 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
2233 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1502133994 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Cordoba, 14 Feb (NA) -- Cordoba Governor Eduardo 
Angeloz today confirmed that he wants to become a presidential 
candidate for the Radical Civic Union [UCR] in 1995 "if the 
party accepts it and if all the instrumental steps that I want 
to impose are accepted by the party." 
  Angeloz denied press reports in which he allegedly conveyed 
to President Carlos Menem his decision to give up his 
presidential candidacy. Angeloz explained: "This confusion is 
not good for our country or anyone. I am the one who, depending 
on my mood, will have to decide in due time if I feel like 
becoming a candidate." 
  Concerning the possibility that Senator Fernando de la Rua 
might actually become the UCR candidate, the governor said: "In 
due time we will see who is in a better position to represent 
the UCR." 
  Angeloz later stressed: "There will not be any internal rift 
within the UCR," although he admitted "the existence of acute, 
hard, and hostile disagreements. The party will remain 
unchanged." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

