<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   De Leon, U.S. Ambassador Inaugurate Fuertes Caminos 94 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1502222894 Guatemala City PRENSA LIBRE in Spanish 12 Feb 
94 p 4 </F>

<F P=103> PA1502222894 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City PRENSA LIBRE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Ramiro de Leon Carpio and U.S. Ambassador 
Marilyn McAfee inaugurated the Fuertes Caminos 94 campaign at 
the municipal stadium in Salama, Baja Verapaz yesterday. The 
purpose of this project is to provice humanitarian aid and real 
opportunities to the communities in the region and to establish 
ties of cooperation. The campaign will also provide training for 
some 300 U.S. National Guard Reserve troops. 
  The U.S. soldiers will work with personnel from the 
Communications, Public Health, and Education Ministries for six 
months. The work will include constructing bridges, buildings, 
and rural roads, digging wells, and carrying out medical and 
educational campaigns. 
  Also present for the inaugural ceremonies were the ministers 
involved in the project, Congress President Vinicio Villar 
Anteu, and several deputies. De Leon Carpio thanked the United 
States for their assistance and asked for support in his fight 
against poverty. 

</TEXT>

