<H3> <TI>   Drug Trafficker Juan David Ochoa Sentenced to Prison </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1502221394 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 0000 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1502221394 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Starting today, a faceless judge has 10 days to 
confirm the Office of the Prosecutor General's request to 
sentence Juan David Ochoa Vasquez to a six and a half year 
prison term. 
  [Begin recording] [Reporter Juan Ortiz] Today, the 
Prosecutor 
General's office sentenced Medellin cartel drug trafficker Juan 
David Ochoa Vasquez to six and a half years in prison, within 
the anticipated sentencing framework for the crimes of illicit 
enrichment, drug trafficking, and collusion. At the hearing, 
which lasted approximately four hours, Deputy Prosecutor General 
Francisco Jose Sintura defined the terms of the negotiation, 
which includes the sentence handed down and the payment of a 
multimillion bond. 
  [Sintura] The Prosecutor General's Office decided to impose 
a 
sentence, after granting the reductions allowed by law for 
confessing, voluntarily surrendering to justice, and reaching an 
agreement with us. 
  [Ortiz] With this sentence, Juan David Ochoa could request 
parole in a little more than a year, since by then he will have 
served 75 percent of his sentence, which started on 16 February 
1991. Today's agreement with Juan David Ochoa Vasquez concludes 
the proceedings against the Ochoa familiy, the first one to 
accept surrendering to the law. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

