  [Text] The Chamber of Deputies has authorized the executive 
branch to send an infantry battalion to Mozambique to join the 
UN peacekeeping force in that country. 
  Deputy Joao Fagundes (Brazilian Democratic Party Movement- 
Roraima), who acted as rapporteur for the Constitution and 
Justice Committee, bears the rank of colonel in the Army 
engineering corps. Fagundes stated that Brazil cannot fail to 
participate in this type of mission, which is internationally 
significant and would show that Brazilian servicemen "are not 
only prepared for war but also to engage in the permanent 
battles for peace." 

