<H3> <TI>   Uncertainty About Inflation Leads to Speculation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1102175594 Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL in Portuguese 
10 Feb 94 p 1--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PY1102175594 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Uncertainty about the date when Real Value Unit 
(URV) will go into force is favoring oligopolies and causing 
large margins of profit to be placed on prices. Sao Paulo 
businessman Marcio Goldfarb, who is a retailer and who deals in 
ready-made clothes, gave this signal of alert. He said 
manufacturers hiked compact disk prices by 90 percent in 
January. To replace products as they are sold, supermarkets are 
paying 50 percent more for them and contracts are being written 
with safeguard clauses. Exporters seek to move up the dates for 
closing exchange contracts and thus have less dollars in cash 
when the day to convert them comes. 
  Pouring his heart out, Ivan Botelho, president of the 
Cataguazes-Leopoldina Group, said: "There is an atmosphere of 
unpatriotic speculation." The inflation rate calculated on 
basis of the IGP-DI [General Prices Index-Domestic Availability] 
totalled 42.19 percent in January. This is the highest since 
March 1990. The IPCA [Expanded Consumer Price Index] rose to 
41.31 percent and the INPC [National Consumer Price Index] to 
41.32 percent. Finance Minister Fernando Henrique Cardoso has 
asserted that he will not subordinate the economic calendar to 
the political one. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

