<H3> <TI>   Lula Says Disagreements Within Party Magnified </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1502133494 Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL in Portuguese 
13 Feb 94 p 2 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PY1502133494 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Editorial: "Magnifying Glass"] </F>
  [Text] Lula [Workers Party, PT, Chairman Luis Inacio da 
Silva] usually says that disagreements within the PT are seen 
like under a magnifying glass. He contends: "The problems are 
not as serious as they are presented to be." 
  Lula believes that the fuss over the [PT] government program 
stemmed from the disclosure of a draft program that had not even 
been assessed by the party's Executive Board. The latter is 
scheduled to meet on 17 February to approve the government 
program. 
  The program then will be publicized so party members can 
debate it at length until the PT national convention on 30 April 
and 1 May, at which Lula will be officially nominated as 
candidate for the presidency. Lula wants, at the same time, to 
debate the program with other parties. 
  With regard to the disagreements with the PT bloc in 
Congress, Lula said the party's Executive Board has not been so 
hard on it as is being said. He recalled that the Executive 
Board authorized the PT bloc to vote on the Social Emergency 
Fund, which was badly needed by [Finance Minister] Fernando 
Henrique Cardoso. 
  Lula notes: "The problem is that summary methods are being 
used for the constitutional revision. There are important 
issues in which our bloc should participate, but conservatives 
have created a steamroller to pass everything they wish. There 
is no way in which our bloc can endorse that, feigning it is 
democratic." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

