<H3> <TI>   Iranian Envoy Summoned in Rushdie Related Protest </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR1602161094 Rotterdam NRC HANDELSBLAD in Dutch 15 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> BR1602161094 </F>
<F P=104>  Rotterdam NRC HANDELSBLAD </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Dutch </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Iranian Ambassador Summoned"] </F>
  [Excerpt] The Hague -- Iranian Ambassador Kazemi-Kamyab was 
summoned to the Foreign Ministry today to hear a strong protest 
following the official statement released by the Iranian 
Government in Teheran that the death sentence against British 
writer Salman Rushdie must indeed be carried out. "The death 
sentence must be carried out, regardless of whether the renegade 
(Rushdie -- NRC HANDELSBLAD editor's note) is repentant," read 
the statement issued yesterday by the official Iranian press 
agency IRNA. The comment was made on the fifth anniversary of 
the death sentence against Rushdie declared by the late 
Ayatollah Khomeyni due to the supposedly blasphemous nature of 
his book The Satanic Verses. 
  Minister Kooijmans wants to push within the Council of 
Ministers for action to be taken against Iran. The Greek 
presidency, according to a spokesman for the Foreign Ministry, 
is considering approaching the Iranian Government on behalf of 
the 12 member states of the European Union, in order to show its 
disgust over the Rushdie affair. The Netherlands does not plan 
to scale down its diplomatic relations with Iran, said the 
spokesman. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

