<H3> <TI>   Dominican Official, Others Cited </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1702024994 Havana Radio Havana Cuba in Spanish 0100 GMT 17 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1702024994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Havana Cuba </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Evening Information Review" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Dominican Deputy Foreign Minister Fabio Herrera has 
asserted that, in his country, citizens of Cuban origin are not 
persecuted and that there are only controls to prevent illegal 
trips to the United States. 
  Danilo Garcia, president of the Association of Cubans in the 
Dominican Republic, said the attempts to leave that country in 
fragile boats are a result of the U.S. refusal to grant them a 
visa to travel to Florida to join their relatives. 
  Observers noted that the attempts by Cuban citizens to 
travel 
illegally to the United States are linked to the favorable 
greeting given to those who use those means, in spite of the 
serious risk to their lives. 

</TEXT>

