<H3> <TI>   Ontario Lawmakers To Promote Aid for Cuba </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1602205394 Havana Radio Havana Cuba in Spanish 1300 GMT 13 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1602205394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Havana Cuba </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Morning Information Review" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Canadian lawmakers from Ontario Province have 
emphasized their intention to help our country in sectors like 
public health, education, and transportation during a meeting 
with Reynaldo Endis, president of the Santiago de Cuba 
Provincial Assembly. The Canadians voiced their willingness to 
conduct in their country a broad campaign of solidarity with 
Cuba. They also expressed their admiration of Cuba's 
achievements in different areas and efforts by the people to 
maintain and defend the gains of the revolution. The Canadian 
lawmakers will conclude their tour of the eastern province of 
Santiago de Cuba after visiting places of economic and social 
interest. 

</TEXT>

