<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Matanzas Crime Rate High Despite Surveillance Units </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1602210694 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1800 
GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1602210694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Approximately 80 percent of the members of the 
agroindustrial production, credit, and services cooperatives in 
Matanzas Province belong to the 174 peasant surveillance 
detachments in that province. More than 9,200 members of the 
National Association of Small Farmers [ANAP] participate in the 
surveillance of livestock and cultivated areas, and 1,250 assist 
the police as volunteers. 
  Despite all this, crime rates in rural areas are still high. 
In the second half of 1993, 330 crimes were reported, of which 
only 50 percent were solved. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

