<H3> <TI>   EZLN on Castellanos Release, War Tax Suspension </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1602134294 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
0435 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1602134294 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Telephone report by Juan Sebastian for the "24 Hours" </F>
newscast] 
  [Text] [Sebastian] Here is a three-point communique that 
has just been issued: 1. To contribute to the prompt start of 
the dialogue for peace with dignity that all Mexicans want, and 
as a sign of the sincere willingness of the EZLN [Zapatist 
National Liberation Army], we hereby announce that on Wednesday, 
16 February 1994, Division General Absalon Castellanos Dominguez 
will be released. 
  2. General Castellanos is to be handed over to Manuel 
Camacho Solis, commissioner for peace and reconciliation in 
Chiapas, and intermediary Father Samuel Luis Garcia in Guadalupe 
Tepeyac, Las Margaritas Municipality, Chiapas. Gen. Castellanos 
Dominguez' health at the time of his release must be verified by 
medical personnel of the International Committee of the Red 
Cross. 
  3. To contribute to detente in the conflict area during the 
time the dialogue for peace with dignity is held, the EZLN 
Clandestine Committee announces its decision to suspend war tax 
collection in areas under the control of our troops effective 17 
February 1994. 
  That is the communique. 
  [Anchorman Jacabo Zabludovsky] This will happen in Guadalupe 
Tepeyac, but no time has been given? 
  [Sebastian] The time was not given. The town is 
approximately five hours from San Cristobal de las Casas. 

</TEXT>

