<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   PRI, PAN Members Clash in Chiapas; 40 injured </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1602161194 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
0435 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1602161194 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Susana Solis from the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] A confrontation between members of the National 
Action Party [PAN] and the Institutional Revolutionary Party 
[PRI] resulted in some 40 people injured in Copainala, Chiapas. 
Four persons had to be hospitalized. 
  The incident occurred when PRI supporters tried to dislodge 
PAN members who had seized the municipal palace to demand the 
removal of Mayor Maurilo Cortazar Aguilar from the municipal 
presidency. The PRI members organized a march through several 
streets of Copainala to express their support for Cortazar. 
Once they reached the municipal building, they tried to 
dislodge the PAN members. The PAN members repelled the 
aggression and left the building following the squabble. 
  The state government has appointed deputy commissions to 
conduct audits in municipalities such as Tuzantan, Huehuetan, 
and Teopisca, where conflicts exist and where municipal palaces 
have already been vacated. 
  The Chanal municipal palace was seized by people demanding 
the mayor's removal. In Cacahoatan, there was a sit-down strike 
in front of the municipal palace today. In addition, peasant 
organizations have taken over at least 100 farms in several 
municipalities. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

