<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   URNG Says Army Preparing Military Offensives </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1702035894 Hamburg DPA in Spanish 2140 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1702035894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mexico City, 16 Feb (DPA) -- The Guatemalan Army is 
allegedly preparing to launch "strong military offensives" in 
the main conflict areas of that Central American country, 
according to statements made today in the Mexican capital by the 
Guatemalan National Revolutionary Unity (URNG). 
  The coalition of guerrilla organizations did not provide 
details of the alleged military plans but said they are 
displaying "the absence of political will at the military staff" 
regarding the next round of peace negotiations scheduled for 
March. 
  While accusing the Army of seeking a "military solution" to 
the Guatemalan crisis, the URNG reiterated "only through 
negotiations can a firm and lasting peace with social justice be 
built in Guatemala." 

</TEXT>

