<F P=100> Chile </F>
<H3> <TI>   UDI Senator Criticizes U.S. Human Rights Report </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1602140594 Santiago Radio Cooperativa Network in Spanish 
2200 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1602140594 </F>
<F P=104>  Santiago Radio Cooperativa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] UDI [Independent Democratic Union] Senator Eugenio 
Cantuarias has criticized the Foreign Ministry's position 
regarding the U.S. State Department report. 
  It should be recalled that U.S. Government officials have 
issued a report stating that during 1993 there were several 
cases of human rights violations in Chile. 
  The U.S. ambassador stated that the report is positive, and 
the Foreign Ministry under secretary said it was better than the 
past one and it acknowledges the efforts made by the current 
government. 
  Cantuarias rejected the report, which he said was 
unacceptable because it represents an intervention in a 
democratic country where the state of law prevails. 
  The UDI legislator said Chilean dignity is trampled on 
whenever U.S. Government officials feel they have the right to 
intervene in domestic affairs and voice their opinion on our 
behavior. 
  Cantuarias then said that the United States has many 
unsolved 
problems and its officials should be busy trying to solve them. 

</TEXT>

