<F P=100> Paraguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Wasmosy Admits Peasants' Plight </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1602212494 Asuncion ABC COLOR in Spanish 16 Feb 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> PY1602212494 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion ABC COLOR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Paraguayan President Juan Carlos Wasmosy yesterday 
acknowledged the existence of poverty and landless peasants, 
adding that the administration will need more funds all the time 
to finance agriculture and development. He said this to 
Argentine Chaco Province officials who visited him at Government 
House. 
  Speaking about the country's needs, the president stated 
that 
in its quest for the wellbeing of all those who live all 
Paraguay, his administration is committed to doing everything it 
can to help the peasants. The president also mentioned other 
urgent issues such as education and health. He explained that 
his administration will do everything it can to satisfy the 
various strata of the population. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

