<H3> <TI>   Additional Reportage on Fujimori's Official Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Fujimori Notes Ties in Speech </H4>
<F P=102> PA1602234394 Lima Panamericana Television Network in Spanish 
1200 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1602234394 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima Panamericana Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Speech by Peruvian President Alberto Fujimori at a dinner </F>
in honor of Colombian President Cesar Gaviria at the Peruvian 
Embassy in Santa Fe de Bogota; date not given; from the "Good 
Morning Peru" newscast -- recorded] 
  [Text] The consolidation of the processes of political and 
economic reforms offers great possibilities for bolstering 
Colombian-Peruvian relations. That is why we fluently speak the 
common language of development today. A civilized way of life 
and democracy have been threatened similarly in Colombia and 
Peru. Colombians and Peruvians, however, have responded readily 
to the scourge of narcotraffickers and terrorists. 
  Our societies know that we will succeed in establishing a 
genuine peace on which we can build true progress and justice. 
I am convinced that as of now, based on the premise of 
consolidating the processes of modernization of our countries, 
perspectives will open so that the existing bilateral mechanisms 
will become more dynamic and high-level contacts between our 
governments will become more frequent and profitable. 
  I am sure, President Gaviria, that Latin America's hour is 
at 
hand. The bases that we are laying today are the cornerstones 
of the building to be shaped by the hands of the new generations 
with a view to the future. Our independence will be sealed with 
our national development. For this new stage of 
Colombian-Peruvian relations and for the realization and 
progress of our peoples, we mutually wish ourselves much 
success. Thank you very much. [applause] 

</TEXT>

