<H3> <TI>   Franco Endorses Cardoso Candidacy, Dismisses Rio Events </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1602235194 Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television in 
Portuguese 2200 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1602235194 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] During a samba parade in Juiz de Fora, Minas 
Gerais, on the evening of 14 February, President Itamar Franco 
spoke for the first time about the incident with model Lilian 
Ramos at Rio de Janeiro Sambodromo [Carnival parade ground]. 
[passage omitted] 
  He said: [Begin recording] I want my right to privacy as 
president and citizen to be respected. There was nothing wrong 
with what happened in Rio de Janeiro. It was just an outward 
show of merriment, a sign of esteem for Rio de Janeiro Carnival. 
I was invited by the chairman of the samba schools association 
and I attended the parade in my capacity as president of the 
Republic. And yet, I also attended it as a human being, as a 
citizen. Therefore, I do not see that I have done anything 
wrong. [end recording] [passage omitted] 
  He added: [Begin recording] For a year and a half we have 
been grappling with inflation, abject poverty, squalor. I would 
like to underscore that Finance Minister Fernando Henrique 
Cardoso has fulfilled his mission as a true patriot. Now, if he 
decides to run for the presidency, he will undoubtedly have my 
support. [end recording]. 

</TEXT>

