<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Machado Ventura Terms UBPC's `Socialist Solution' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1702225194 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 2050 GMT 
17 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1702225194 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Basic Cooperative Production Units [UBPC's] are 
a socialist solution in keeping with our reality, said Politburo 
member Jose Ramon Machado Ventura after being informed that this 
UBPC experiment is doing well in Guane Municipality, Pinar del 
Rio Province. From a talk with workers at La Catalina UBPC, he 
learned that they expect to receive over 800 pesos per capita 
profit at the end of this year, in addition to daily advances 
for their work. 
  Machado noted the enthusiasm that prevails in La Catalina 
because of the results obtained by this UBPC in the short time 
it has been in existence, and emphasized the need to put into 
practice the profitability schema, which will be able to 
systematically measure productivity. 
  Machado Ventura also exchanged views with workers and 
leaders 
of the Camilo Cienfuegos livestock UPBC in Guane Municipality, 
where he expressed appreciation for that UBPC's good performance. 

</TEXT>

