<F P=101> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   PANPRA `Leanings' Precipitate Leader Resignations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1702215894 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1700 
GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1702215894 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Agronomist Roosevelt (Saindic) officially announced 
his resignation from PANPRA [National Progressive Revolutionary 
Party of Haiti] leadership after having discontinued 
participation in their activities as of May 1993. The 
resignation letter of Roosevelt (Saindic) mentions deep 
opposition to his management style from several members of the 
party, especially concerning work methods, strategy, and the 
party's current political leanings. 
  The resignation of (Saindic) from PANPRA's leadership, 
follows that of several other members of this political party 
including Georges Weirleigh, Arnold Antonin, and Claude Elisma. 

</TEXT>

