<H3> <TI>   Presidency Spokesman Danilo Lacayo Resigns </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1702143694 Managua Sistema Nacional de Television Network 
in Spanish 0100 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1702143694 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua Sistema Nacional de Television Network 
in Spanish 0100 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Erica Ramirez from the "National Newscast"] </F>
  [Text] Presidency Spokesman Dr. Danilo Lacayo confirmed 
today that he has tendered his resignation to President Chamorro. 
  [Begin Lacayo recording] I leave with affection and respect 
for the president to dedicate myself to other tasks. Wherever I 
may be, I will always cooperate with the national project, as I 
have stated in my letter of resignation. [end recording] 
  Dr. Lacayo appraised the government's performance during the 
past years. 
  [Begin Lacayo recording] The president of the Nicaraguan 
people has performed an enormous task by ending a war, entering 
a period of peace, and building such a difficult democracy. The 
president has done a great job. Obviously, this is not the 
most perfect government in the world, but we can say that this 
administration has given us hope for the first time. It has 
helped us to achieve reconciliation. Above all, the president 
of the Republic of Nicaragua is determined to build democratic 
values and institutions and -- as she has always said -- she is 
carrying out a mission. It is a difficult mission but, it is 
the mission that she was given. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

