<H3> <TI>   * Mexicans Finance Peanut Production </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P20384A </F>
<F P=103> 94P20384A </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:CSO 

  [Editorial Report] Managua LA PRENSA in Spanish of 21 
January 1994 on page 8 reports that Mexican investors have 
expressed interest in purchasing the Chinandega peanut crop due 
to a drop in production in Mexico. The Chinandega peanut crop is 
expected to yield 150,000 quintals. The Mexicans will pay $20 
per quintal after it has been processed. The article explains 
that Anagsa, an agroindustrial enterprise, is purchasing 
harvesting equipment with Mexican financing. According to local 
producers, Corinto port activity, local employment, and industry 
are expected to grow as a result of the investment. 

</TEXT>

