<H3> <TI>   * New Development Center Established </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P20384B </F>
<F P=103> 94P20384B </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:CSO 

  [Editorial Report] Managua EL NUEVO DIARIO in Spanish of 29 
January 1994 on page 6 reports that the first development center 
in Valle de Sebaco has been created in order to facilitate the 
marketing of the area's products. The article reports that small 
and medium producers will be able to rent machinery at low cost 
from the Ministry of Agriculture and Livestock (MAG) and receive 
training from the Development Foundation (Funde). Producers will 
eventually be able to form cooperatives and obtain 
"unconventional" loans. MAG Deputy Minister Julio Rivera 
explains that there are currently 44 development centers 
nationwide serving approximately 50,000 peasant families. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

