<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   * Plans for Ginger, Sweet Potato Financing Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P20384C </F>
<F P=103> 94P20384C </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:CSO 

  [Editorial Report] Managua LA PRENSA in Spanish of 1 
February 1994 on page 4 reports that El Rama farmers are seeking 
investors for ginger and sweet potato. The Ministry of 
Agriculture and Livestock (MAG) is negotiating a $50,000 
investment from the Italian Government to support the 
cultivation and export of the two products, according to the 
article. Patrick Bolanos, president of the Nontraditional 
Products Association, says that Greek investors are planning to 
purchase ginger and sweet potato at the port of La Esperanza on 
the Atlantic Coast. The article reports that over 1,600 manzanas 
of ginger, sweet potato, yuca, and other nontraditional products 
will be planted this year with international financial 
assistance. 

</TEXT>

