<F P=100> Uruguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Reports on Economic Activity </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1702195794 </F>
<F P=103> PY1702195794 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic activities in Uruguay through 17 February: 
  The Central Bank reported that the state registered a $654.2 
million deficit in the January-November 1993 period. This was 
the result of the public sector's nonfinancial deficit of $194.5 
million and the parafiscal deficit of $459.7 million. 
(Montevideo LA MANANA in Spanish 11 Feb 94 p 38) 
  The European-Argentine group Miniphone will invest $21 
million in the next 24 months on the installation of a mobile 
cellular telephone system nationwide. This service will benefit 
80 percent of the urban population and 70 percent of the rural. 
(Montevideo LA MANANA in Spanish 11 Feb 94 p 12) 
  The public sector's deficit increased $69 million in 
November 
1993, raising the cumulative deficit in the past 11 months to 
$152 million, more than 1 percent of the GDP. (Montevideo EL 
OBSERVADOR ECONOMICO in Spanish 11 Feb 94 p 10) 

</TEXT>

